{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κατα-σείω</b>, <br /> <i>future</i> <b>-σείσω</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Art.” 43 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> <b>-σέσεικα</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Philemo Comicus [{4-3rd c.BC}] 84 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]:—<b>shake down, throw down</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" οἰκοδομήματος ἐπὶ μέγα 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.76 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τεῖχος, τοῦ τείχους ἐπὶ μέγα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “An.” 1.19.2, 2.23.1; σεισμὸς κ. τὴν πόλιν Ae|. “VH” 6.7:\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, <b>fall down</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 2.512 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; of a lion's mane, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" αὐχένος ἐκ λασίοιο Χαίτη -εσείετο 2nd c.AD: Pancrates Epicus “POxy.” 1085.21 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: <i>metaphorically</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" κ. ἀκροατοῦ ὦτα Philostratus Sophista [{2-3rd c.AD}] “Vitae Sophistarum” 2.29; νόμους 6th c.AD: Procopius Caesariensis Historicus “Historia Arcana” 27.33; κατέσεισεν ἅπαντα καὶ κατεβρόντησε Eunapius Historicus [{4-5th c.AD}] “Fragmenta Historica - HGM” p.256 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator; ἕως κατέσεισε\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] until he <b>laid</b> him <b>on the floor</b> (with drinking), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 8, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus [same place], 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 10.431c. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>impel, drive headlong</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" νεανίσκον εἰς τὸν μανιώδη καὶ σφαλερὸν τῆς βασιλείας ἔρωτα Eunapius Historicus [{4-5th c.AD}] “Fragmenta Historica - HGM” p.235 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator, compare p.267 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator:\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, πρὸς τὸ λέγειν κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] p.223 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> in Surgery, <b>treat by shaking</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 42:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 43. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> κατασείσας τὴν χεῖρα <b>with a motion</b> of the hand, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Acts.19.33; κ. ἱκετηρίας 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Bellum Judaicum” 2.21.8 \">NT+1st c.AD+</a>]; κ. τὰ ἱμάτια, by way of signal, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pomp.” 73: more frequently with _dative_, κ. τῇ Χειρί\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>] <b>beckon</b> with the hand, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.78.3, 3rd c.AD: Heliodorus Scriptor Eroticus 10.7; κ. τῇ Χειρὶ σιγᾶν “Act.Ap.” 12.17; κ. τῷ λύχνῳ ἅμα λέγων τὸν λόγον “PMag.Lond.” 46.453; κ. ὀθόναις 3rd c.AD: Heliodorus Scriptor Eroticus 9.6 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, κ. τινί <b>beckon</b> to another, as a sign for him to be silent, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Cyr.” 5.4.4; κ. τισὶν ἐπεξιέναι 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Antiquitates Judaicae” 17.10.2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but also, <b>shake the head</b> in token of contempt, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Vit.” p.37 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2678","accentedUnicode":"κατασείω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0383","matchingForm":"ἀνασείω","stepTransliteration":"anaseiō","gloss":"to incite","_zh_tw_Gloss":"煽動, 挑唆","_es_Gloss":"incitar","_zh_Gloss":"煽动, 挑唆"},{"strongNumber":"G1286","matchingForm":"διασείω","stepTransliteration":"diaseiō","gloss":"to extort","_zh_tw_Gloss":"強暴","_es_Gloss":"extorsionar ","_zh_Gloss":"强暴"},{"strongNumber":"G2596